0.2.0-beta - 6 July 2007 (r6087)
==================================================
-- <wysywig> tag now supports dynamic "name" attribute and also supports "given_value" functionality
-- adding phpdoc header to modules
-- changing header: making the name more clear and making it to play nicely with phpDocumentor
-- new wysiwyg attribute "profile" for <wysiwyg> tag, using this attribute you can specify which settings section will be used for this instance of richedit component
-- WYSIWIG TinyMCE adding functionality for multiple config and editors at one page. Static property added for including editor js script only once.
-- Adding TinyMCE v.2.2.1 support with iBrowser.
-- Adding FCKeditor v 2.4.2 PHP "File uploading" enabled by default.
-- <richedit> alias tag for <wysiwyg> added

